<hl>
<seg id=1> Foreign cooperation with the Chinese building materials industry has developed rapidly </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Beijing, March 19th, by Jianmin Li- Enhancing foreign cooperation is an important measure for the State Building Materials Industry Bureau in order to speed up the development of the building materials industry. The realm of foreign funds utilization has been rapidly increased. Currently, the total amount of foreign fund utilization in this industry has approached 500 million US dollars. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> An official in charge from the State Building Materials Industry said to the reporters that, currently, a group of cement construction projects have been put into production one after another, such as, the State Building Materials Industry utilized the loans from the International Bank and the Asian Development Bank to conduct constructions in Tongling County of Anhui province, Xiangxiang of Hunan province, etc. </seg>
<seg id=4> The scope of foreign funds utilization is rapidly developing towards new building materials, advanced technologies, improving manufacturing of building materials, etc. </seg>
<seg id=5> Using 100 million US dollars from an Italian concessional export loan, the high level sanitary ceramics technology reform project is making a vigorous progress in Shaanxi, Shandong, Guandong, Jielin, Hunan and other provinces. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Recently, the State Building Materials Industry signed bilateral corporation agreements with the government departments of Holland, Germany, Thailand, Greece, Australia, Japan, France, Denmark, etc., Resulting in a rapid increase in the number of foreign corporate partners. </seg>
<seg id=7> Last year, the foreign exchange earning from the Chinese building material products exceeded 210 million US dollars, exporting 12,000,000 tons of cement, an increase of 46% more than the year before which is the best year in history. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Besides, China imported advanced kilning production lines from overseas during the past several years, and built up large modernized cement enterprises in Yidong, Linguo, Huaihai, Njuzhou, etc. adding 22,000,000 tons more to the annual production volume. </seg>
</p>
